-- Lira Pierces 100-day Moving Average Against Euro
-- B y   S e l c u k   G o k o l u k   a n d   A s h   K u m a r
-- 2012-09-03T14:08:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-03/lira-pierces-100-day-moving-average-against-euro.html
Turkish currency retreats less than
0.1% to 2.2877 per euro, weakening 14th day in 16 to the lowest
on closing basis since June 29.
* RSI at 71.8; above 70 for 4 days; last time below 30 on July
20: Bloomberg data
* 50-day moving average 2.2327; 100-day MA 2.2730; 200-day MA
2.3279
* A “lot of the move” is down to euro strength relative to
eastern European currencies, Christian Lawrence, currency
strategist at Rabobank in London, says in e-mailed comments
today
** Poland’s zloty falls 3.2% against euro since Aug. 6;
Hungary’s forint retreats 2.6% in same period
* “Turkey’s central bank will keep a dovish bias ahead and so I
dont expect any rapid appreciation,” Lawrence says
* NOTE:  Inflation slowed to 8.9% in August from 9.1% in July as
food and transport prices rose, Turkish statistics agency says
on its website today
** Median est. of 5 economists surveyed by Bloomberg was 8.3%:
Bloomberg
** Core inflation, which excludes food and non-alcoholic
beverages, declined to 7.2% in August from 7.5% mth earlier
* NOTE: European Central Bank President  Mario Draghi  may provide
details of plan to shore up euro on Sept. 6 at monetary policy
